text: I played the Atraxa precon yesterday at my LGS against an elfball deck and my son's Nikya of the Old Ways and I was reminded how strong that deck can be out of the box. The only reason I didn't win was because I didn't kill him early on when I could because I didn't want him to have to sit out the game (he was the first out in a previous game).
My son hit me for 130 damage and I survived at 12 the previous turn...
Atraxa itself is just so powerful... if there isn't an [[Dictate of Erebos]] sort of effect out, it just has a tendency to define the game.

Here's a question...at my LGS yesterday a friend was playing basically a 'pile of good cards' Tasigur deck, which he admitted was something he threw together because he wanted to play Tasigur. Afterwards he asked me to look through his deck and give my thoughts on ways to come up an actual strategy/theme, since most of his decks tend to be goodstuff piles (he plays cEDH as well).

My first take was, I can't give you any comments on the cards since without a theme you'd just be swapping one good card for another, but we discussed possibly Superfriends, which he liked, or I also said 'attack trigger tribal' which would be creatures or effects that happen when you attack, since that would put natural limiters on the deck and let him explore outside his comfort zone. He was looking for something far less powerful and consistent than what he does with cEDH.

I'm curious how how other folks tend to answer these types of questions.
